He was disappointed,because he did love children...

423
00:21:47,216 --> 00:21:48,741
更别说是自己的孩子了
his in particular...

424
00:21:48,885 --> 00:21:51,147
但他对于流产一事也没有提出反对
but he went along with the abortion idea.

425
00:21:52,320 --> 00:21:54,380
黛安的哥哥 鲍勃 是位医生
Diane's brother, Bob,was a doctor.

426
00:21:54,523 --> 00:21:58,392
我还记得当时我在办公室
I do recall being at the office

427
00:21:58,528 --> 00:22:00,393
她打电话给我
when I got a call from her.

428
00:22:01,431 --> 00:22:02,830
声音听起来很焦急
She was quite desperate,

429
00:22:02,966 --> 00:22:07,026
她说她怀孕了 可自己今年已经42岁了
because she was about 42 and said that she was pregnant,

430
00:22:07,170 --> 00:22:08,660
这孩子是个意外
that it wasn't planned,

431
00:22:08,805 --> 00:22:12,138
她担心孩子会有唐氏综合症
that she was desperately worried about Down syndrome.

432
00:22:12,276 --> 00:22:14,267
当时的我 我想
And at the time I was, I think,

433
00:22:14,411 --> 00:22:18,541
是把一个生命看得比病人的选择更重要的
a bit more pro-life than pro-choice,

434
00:22:18,682 --> 00:22:20,115
所以你妈妈打来电话的时候
so when your mother called,

435
00:22:20,251 --> 00:22:21,810
我说服了她
I believe that I steered her

436
