00:34:54,523 --> 00:34:56,116
『他个子不高 他是红发』
"and he's short,and he has red hair. "

680
00:34:56,257 --> 00:34:58,316
而你出生时头发就是淡红色的
And you were born with bright red hair.

681
00:34:58,459 --> 00:35:02,260
我猛地想起当时老妈非常在意
I instantly flashed back to Mom making a huge deal

682
00:35:02,397 --> 00:35:03,624
你是红头发这事
about you having red hair.

683
00:35:03,764 --> 00:35:05,130
这就和你撒谎的时候
It's like when you're lying about something,

684
00:35:05,267 --> 00:35:06,428
会不停地强调假话一样
you overplay it?

685
00:35:06,569 --> 00:35:08,298
她总是不停地说
She had gone on and on

686
00:35:08,438 --> 00:35:10,804
萨拉是红头发这事太奇怪了
about how weird it is that Sarah has red hair.

687
00:35:10,940 --> 00:35:12,100
『太怪了！』
"It's so odd!

688
00:35:12,241 --> 00:35:15,176
『可能是我堂妹玛格丽特安妮是红发的关系吧』
"I guess my cousin Margaret-Anne has red hair. "

689
00:35:15,311 --> 00:35:16,538
这事突然就闪回到我的脑海中
And that struck me,

690
00:35:16,678 --> 00:35:17,975
接着我看见他一头红发的照片
and then I saw him with the red hair,

691
00:35:18,113 --> 00:35:19,513
所以我想...
and I really did think...

692
00:35:19,649 --> 00:35:21,277
我当时真的觉得这是真的
I really thought it was true.

693
00:35:22,885 --> 00:35:25,548
有时候 我真的开始相信那是真的
So at some point, I think I did start to believe it was true

694
00:35:25,689 --> 00:35:28,214
开始想是不是该有人把真相告诉你
and thought someone should say something to you.

695
00:35:28,359 --> 00:35:31,349
我记得我们几个人凑在一起讨论过
I feel like we all had a discussion about it at some point,

696
00:35:31,494 --> 00:35:33,326
当然 不包括你
"we all" being everyone but you.

697
00:35:33,464 --> 00:35:35,159
约翰尼说我是个大嘴巴
And I think Johnny said I had a big mouth

698
00:35:35,299 --> 00:35:37,358
我可能会把这事告诉你
and that I was probably gonna tell you or something.

699
00:35:37,501 --> 00:35:39,493
我和他说『我觉得我们应该告诉她』
And I was saying,"I think we should tell her. "

700
00:35:41,005 --> 00:35:42,837
现在 让我们把时间向前推进一点
Now, I think we should leap forward to a point

701
00:35:42,974 --> 00:35:45,204
在黛安去世几年后
several years after Diane's death,

702
00:35:45,943 --> 00:35:49,107
晚餐桌上的那个陈年笑话
when the jokes with her family round the dinner table

703
00:35:49,247 --> 00:35:50,679
似乎也不再好笑了
were not so funny,

704
00:35:51,381 --> 00:35:52,543
当话题开始变得严肃
and since it went further

705
00:35:52,685 --> 00:35:54,778
而多伦多剧团里那个可能的父亲
and named the member of the cast of Toronto

706
00:35:54,920 --> 00:35:57,081
身份正日渐明朗
who was her possible parent,

707
00:35:57,223 --> 00:36:00,818
她觉得是时候迈出关键一步了
she decided it was time to take the plunge.

708
00:36:00,961 --> 00:36:03,359
她打电话给杰弗 问他可不可以见面
She phoned Geoff and asked if they could meet.

709
00:36:04,963 --> 00:36:06,022
你打电话来...
You called...

710
00:36:07,399 --> 00:36:10,631
我们安排了见面
and we arranged to meet,

711
00:36:10,771 --> 00:36:13,638
你问我当年在蒙特利尔发生的事
and you wanted to know about that time in Montreal.

712
00:36:13,774 --> 00:36:15,743
我当时把手搭在你的肩上 心想
I remember putting my arm around you,and I thought,

713
00:36:15,877 --> 00:36:17,673
『哦 天啊 希望我没做得太过』
"Oh, boy, I hope that isn't too forward or something. "

714
00:36:17,811 --> 00:36:20,974
我开始想起你问我的那些事
And I remember recounting some of the same tales.

715
00:36:21,114 --> 00:36:23,446
那些我遗忘了很久的关于黛安的事
I hadn't really thought about Diane for a long time,

716
00:36:23,583 --> 00:36:26,314
我当时心里挺难过的
so I recall being pretty sad.

717
00:36:27,121 --> 00:36:30,682
从我18岁起 就总有人说
So, since I was 18, there was this rumor

718
00:36:30,825 --> 00:36:32,952
你是我的亲生父亲
that you were my biological father.

719
00:36:34,695 --> 00:36:35,992
这事听起来是不是很奇怪
It's been this bizarre thing.

720
00:36:36,130 --> 00:36:39,498
我总在想 到底是从什么地方传开的
It's like, how that rumor began,where did it come from?

721
00:36:39,635 --> 00:36:41,193
所以我就想问你一下
And I just wanted to ask you about that.

722
00:36:41,336 --> 00:36:44,305
你和我妈在交往过程中发生过『那种』事情吗
Was there ever anything romantic in your relationship with Mom,

723
00:36:44,439 --> 00:36:46,805
还是说你们只是普通朋友
or was it always just friendship?

724
00:36:48,778 --> 00:36:50,108
我们只是普通朋友
Uh, it was friendship.

725
00:36:51,879 --> 00:36:54,145
我还记得你说...
I remember you saying...

726
00:36:54,284 --> 00:36:56,912
你说那句话时我很惊讶
being surprised at you saying,

727
00:36:57,053 --> 00:37:01,319
『我们家里的每个人都知道』
"It's common knowledge in my family that, uh, my...

728
00:37:01,457 --> 00:37:03,448
『我妈当时爱上你了』
"that my mom was in love with you. "

729
00:37:03,593 --> 00:37:06,118
我当时很吃惊
And I was taken aback at that.

730
00:37:08,832 --> 00:37:09,958
我觉得有点触动
I was touched.

731
00:37:17,775 --> 00:37:20,301
杰弗坚持说
Everything Geoff said suggested he was certain

732
00:37:20,445 --> 00:37:23,504
黛安没有对迈克尔不忠
that Diane had stayed faithful to Michael.

733
00:37:24,714 --> 00:37:28,482
但她脑中的疑问之种仍在生长
But that seed of doubt had grown even larger in her mind.

734
00:37:29,321 --> 00:37:32,813
她觉得他是一个可爱 坦诚 慷慨的人
She thought he was a lovely,open,and generous person,

735
00:37:33,625 --> 00:37:36,254
但她也觉得他藏着秘密
and yet she felt he was hiding something.

736
00:37:36,962 --> 00:37:40,797
但她又一次放开了追问的那条线
But, once again, she let the story lie.

737
00:37:40,933 --> 00:37:43,595
这个谜团仍然没能解开
And so the conundrum remained just that.

738
00:37:44,437 --> 00:37:48,636
一天 她在多伦多偶然遇见一位蒙特利尔的制作人
One day, she chanced to meet a Montreal producer in Toronto

739
00:37:48,775 --> 00:37:52,574
提到自己要去蒙特利尔几天
and mentions that she's going to Montreal in a couple of days,

740
00:37:52,712 --> 00:37:55,614
那位制作人说『你到蒙特利尔以后』
and the producer says, "While you're there,

741
00:37:55,749 --> 00:37:58,547
『可以和哈利・高金见个面』
"you might want to meet up with Harry Gulkin.

742
00:37:58,685 --> 00:38:00,585
『他也是位电影制作人』
"He's an important film producer

743
00:38:00,721 --> 00:38:03,315
『在你母亲做选角导演时与她合作过』
"that your mother worked with as a casting director

744
00:38:03,457 --> 00:38:07,087
『或许可以帮助你了解下你母亲的事』
"and can probably tell you more about your mother in those days. "

745
00:38:07,228 --> 00:38:08,923
萨拉很高兴
And Sarah is very pleased.

746
00:38:09,063 --> 00:38:10,188
对自己出生前母亲的生活
She always likes to hear

747
00:38:10,330 --> 00:38:12,959
她总是充满好奇
about her mother's life before Sarah's birth,

748
00:38:13,101 --> 00:38:15,262
同时她也觉得
and she also realized that this Harry

749
00:38:15,403 --> 00:38:17,064
哈利可能
may be able to shed more light

750
00:38:17,205 --> 00:38:20,265
会对母亲是否和当时的剧组成员有外遇一事
on the possibility of her mother having had an affair

751
00:38:20,408 --> 00:38:21,706
略知一二
with a member of the cast.

752
00:38:21,844 --> 00:38:23,902
所以她拨了哈利的电话
And so she phones Harry

753
00:38:24,045 --> 00:38:27,483
问他是否愿意和自己聊聊
and asks if she could get together with him for a chat.

754
00:38:27,617 --> 00:38:29,311
嗨 萨拉 谢谢你主动与我联系
Hi, Sarah,and a warm welcome.

755
00:38:29,984 --> 00:38:32,453
艾妮说你想见我
Arnie Gelbart told me you would like to see me.

756
00:38:32,588 --> 00:38:34,819
正好我也想见你
That's good,because I would love to see you.

757
00:38:34,958 --> 00:38:37,323
今天下午我会在办公室
I can be reached in my office this afternoon,

758
00:38:37,459 --> 00:38:38,790
或者你可以在白天时发邮件给我
or email me here during the day.

759
00:38:38,928 --> 00:38:40,260
嗨 哈利
Hi, Harry.Great to hear from you.

760
00:38:40,397 --> 00:38:43,525
我一直记得我妈总是用仰慕的语气谈论你
I always remember my mom talking about you with such affection.

761
00:38:43,667 --> 00:38:45,329
很高兴终于能和你见面
It'd be great to finally meet you.

762
00:38:45,468 --> 00:38:48,335
下午3：45有空到Ex-Centris外喝杯咖啡么
Would you be free at 3:45 to meet at Ex-Centris for a coffee?

763
00:38:48,471 --> 00:38:49,530
他同意了
He agrees,

764
00:38:49,673 --> 00:38:52,335
几天后 他们在一家餐馆见了面
and a couple of days later,they meet in a restaurant.

765
00:38:52,475 --> 00:38:54,239
接下来发生的事
What happens next is what I can remember

766
00:38:54,378 --> 00:38:57,107
我只能回忆起与萨拉有关的部分
of Sarah's relating the event.

767
00:39:07,492 --> 00:39:09,517
你说你一直很想见我
and you said that you had wanted to meet me

768
00:39:09,661 --> 00:39:13,428
因为你的母亲常常提到我
because your mother had talked about me a lot.

769
00:39:14,300 --> 00:39:17,133
接着我们又聊了很多
And then we talked about a million things.

770
00:39:17,270 --> 00:39:20,534
你说你十五岁时不得不退学
You told me how you had quit school at 15,

771
00:39:20,672 --> 00:39:22,641
最主要的一个原因是
and that one of the dominating reasons

772
00:39:22,775 --> 00:39:24,241
你当时的政治立场
was your politics at the time

773
00:39:24,376 --> 00:39:26,743
以及你打算加入阶级斗争军的行列
and your desire to join the class struggle.

774
00:39:26,879 --> 00:39:28,346
我觉得这很有意思
That struck me as very interesting,

775
00:39:28,481 --> 00:39:30,210
因为我曾经做过一模一样的事
because I had done exactly the same thing.

776
00:39:30,350 --> 00:39:33,650
在那次谈话后 我们的关系变得很好
And we became very close during that conversation.

777
00:39:33,787 --> 00:39:36,187
我们在彼此身上找到了许多共同点
We found a whole number of things in common

778
00:39:36,323 --> 00:39:39,758
情感 反应 回应他人的方式
in terms of feelings, reactions, response.

779
00:39:39,893 --> 00:39:41,326
我记得你说 第一眼见到他
And I remember you saying,as soon as you met him,

780
00:39:41,462 --> 00:39:43,793
就觉得有种莫名的安定感
you felt at ease with him in a certain way,

781
00:39:43,930 --> 00:39:45,900
也正是因为这种安定感
and because you felt so at ease with him,

782
00:39:46,034 --> 00:39:48,059
让你决定问他是否知道
you had decided to ask him if he knew anything

783
00:39:48,203 --> 00:39:52,229
杰弗・博斯是你生父这一说法的真实性
about this rumor about Geoff Bowes being your dad.

784
00:39:53,140 --> 00:39:55,974
你问他『你有没有听说过』
You asked him the question,"Have you ever heard anything

785
00:39:56,111 --> 00:39:59,274
『我妈在蒙特利尔演出时有了外遇』
"about my mom having had an affair while she was in Montreal?"

786
00:39:59,414 --> 00:40:00,473
你抬起头来对我说
You looked up and you said,

787
00:40:00,616 --> 00:40:02,880
『你觉得是杰弗・博斯么？』
"Do you think it was Geoff Bowes?"

788
00:40:03,786 --> 00:40:05,276
我说『不』
So I said, "No. "

789
00:40:06,022 --> 00:40:08,217
你又说『那你知道是谁么？』
She said, "Do you know who it was?"

790
00:40:08,357 --> 00:40:09,688
我说『我知道』
And I said, "Yes. "

791
00:40:09,824 --> 00:40:12,122
『我知道杰弗・博斯不是你父亲』
"No, I know that Geoff Bowes isn't your dad. "

792
00:40:12,260 --> 00:40:13,250
你说『你怎么知道？』
And you said, "How do you know that?"

793
00:40:13,396 --> 00:40:14,795
他说『因为我才是你父亲』
And he said, "Cause I'm your dad. "

794
00:40:16,066 --> 00:40:19,934
他说『可能 而非也许』
He said,"It's possible, not probable. "

795
00:40:20,070 --> 00:40:21,902
你在电话里就是这么和我说的吧
I think those were the exact words you said to me on the phone.

796
00:40:22,040 --> 00:40:23,063
是么
Were they?

797
00:40:23,206 --> 00:40:26,436
他说『我以为你是因为这个才来找我的』
He said, "I thought that's why you wanted to speak to me,

798
00:40:26,576 --> 00:40:30,067
『因为你妈妈和我之间的事』
"because your mom and I had an affair. "

799
00:40:30,212 --> 00:40:33,877
『事实上 她是和我外遇了』
"In fact, she had an affair with me. "

800
00:40:34,018 --> 00:40:35,713
我说『是我』
And I said, "Me. "

801
00:40:40,625 --> 00:40:42,252
你愣了一下
So you stopped for a moment,

802
00:40:42,393 --> 00:40:44,826
又说『你现在还这么觉得么』
then you said, "Do you still think so?"

803
00:40:44,961 --> 00:40:46,794
我说『在和你聊天...』
And I said, "After talking to you

804
00:40:46,932 --> 00:40:50,095
『近距离看着你将近三小时之后 我可以确定』
"and looking at you for close to three hours, yes. "

805
00:40:50,235 --> 00:40:51,600
我说『你觉得呢？』
I said, "What do you think?"

806
00:40:51,737 --> 00:40:55,139
而你说『嗯 我也觉得是这样』
And you said, "Yeah, I think so, too. "

807
00:40:55,275 --> 00:40:57,241
萨拉哑口无言
Sarah is speechless.

808
00:40:58,342 --> 00:41:01,471
他本想知道更多关于杰弗的事
She's come all this way to find out about Geoff,

809
00:41:02,482 --> 00:41:04,950
却意外地和母亲的情人共处了一下午
and now she's sitting with her mother's lover.

810
00:41:13,693 --> 00:41:17,595
那是1978年2月底的事了
It was late February of 1978.

811
00:41:17,731 --> 00:41:20,131
我当时心情有些沮丧
I was sort of mildly depressed...

812
00:41:20,267 --> 00:41:22,668
隆冬时节 无所事事 孤身一人
midwinter, nothing to do,living alone...

813
00:41:23,404 --> 00:41:26,168
我就决定去中央剧院看戏
and I decided to go to the Centaur Theatre

814
00:41:26,307 --> 00:41:29,764
大卫・费那里奥的新剧正在公演
to see the latest production of David Fennario.

815
00:41:29,909 --> 00:41:32,208
我刚进去不久
So I went down there,and after a minute,

816
00:41:32,346 --> 00:41:33,746
演员们就登台了
as the cast came on stage,

817
00:41:33,882 --> 00:41:38,251
出现在眼前的一位女士让我呆住了
I was transfixed by this glorious lady who was on stage.

818
00:41:38,386 --> 00:41:39,853
是完全被迷住了
Really just bowled over.

819
00:41:39,988 --> 00:41:43,947
戏落幕的时候 我仍然觉得很害羞
When the play was over,I still had certain reserves of shyness,

820
00:41:44,092 --> 00:41:45,490
从头到尾我都在害羞
which still remain,

821
00:41:45,626 --> 00:41:47,857
所以我没有去后台
so I didn't go backstage,

822
00:41:47,997 --> 00:41:49,793
而是打算睡前
and I decided to have a nightcap

823
00:41:49,931 --> 00:41:53,527
去那家『三驾马车』小酒馆喝一杯
at what I considered then my geriatric bar, the Troika.

824
00:41:53,669 --> 00:41:54,601
我点了杯饮料
I ordered a drink,

825
00:41:54,737 --> 00:41:56,500
酒吧里放着伤感的俄罗斯三重奏
and they had a schmaltzy Russian trio,

826
00:41:56,639 --> 00:41:58,163
五分钟后
and after about five minutes,

827
00:41:58,307 --> 00:42:00,833
刚才舞台上的那位女士
who walks in but this lady who had been on stage

828
00:42:00,978 --> 00:42:02,171
和其它剧组演员一起走了进来
with some other cast members,

829
00:42:02,311 --> 00:42:04,040
我心想『哦 上帝啊』
so I figure, "Oh, my God,"

830
00:42:04,180 --> 00:42:07,150
我便起身混进了那群人当中
and I sort of sidled into the middle of the group,

831
00:42:07,284 --> 00:42:08,980
不时地开口
and I was able to inveigle myself

832
00:42:09,120 --> 00:42:11,178
插上一两句话
into the conversation to some degree,

833
00:42:11,321 --> 00:42:14,689
我试图找到和黛安单独说话的机会
and I did try to separate Diane from the group.

834
00:42:14,826 --> 00:42:16,918
但一小时后 我放弃了尝试
But after about an hour, it really was hopeless.

835
00:42:17,060 --> 00:42:19,188
这种事不会发生的
It wasn't gonna happen.

836
00:42:21,332 --> 00:42:23,028
黛安离开『三驾马车』的时候
When Diane left the Troika,

837
00:42:23,168 --> 00:42:25,033
我跟上了那一群人
I walked with them and with her,

838
00:42:25,170 --> 00:42:28,868
我问黛安是否能单独说句话
and I was trying again to separate Diane,

839
00:42:29,008 --> 00:42:30,031
她的回答是『不』
and she said, "No,

840
00:42:30,175 --> 00:42:31,972
『不过我们可以明晚再见』
"but we can meet tomorrow night. "

841
00:42:32,110 --> 00:42:35,603
在剧组留在蒙特利尔演出的剩下的日子里
We met every night after that for the remainder of the run,

842
00:42:35,748 --> 00:42:39,184
我们每天晚上都会见面 感觉彼此被对方强烈地吸引
and there was a very strong mutual attraction...

843
00:42:39,318 --> 00:42:40,945
那种感觉非常 非常强烈
very, very powerful thing.

844
00:42:42,222 --> 00:42:44,815
哈利每天都会等在楼梯下面
Harry would be down at the bottom of the stairs,

845
00:42:44,957 --> 00:42:46,015
我们都呆在剧院二层
we were in the upstairs theater,

846
00:42:46,158 --> 00:42:47,490
化妆间也在那上面
and our dressing room was up there,

847
00:42:47,627 --> 00:42:50,118
他让我想到那些旧百老汇电影里
